## 2. Component library

### Code

- **No local component library** — UI from `@astryxdesign/core` (148 components)
- **Pages:** `src/app/pages/` — Server Components by default
- **Client islands:** colocated `"use client"` files (see `home.tsx` + `home-form.tsx`)
- **No Storybook** — discover via Astryx CLI

Import pattern (deep imports, not barrel):

```tsx
import { Button } from "@astryxdesign/core/Button";
import { Card } from "@astryxdesign/core/Card";
import { HStack, VStack } from "@astryxdesign/core/Layout";
import { Heading, Text } from "@astryxdesign/core/Text";
import { Badge } from "@astryxdesign/core/Badge";
import { TextInput } from "@astryxdesign/core/TextInput";
```

Discovery before inventing UI:

```bash
vp run astryx -- build "<screen description>"
vp run astryx -- component <Name>
vp run astryx -- search "<pattern>"
```

### Figma → Astryx mapping

When screen frames are added to Figma, map components via MCP + CLI:

| Figma intent | Astryx target |
|--------------|---------------|
| Button | `Button` (`variant="primary"` \| `"secondary"`) |
| Card / panel | `Card` + `bg-surface` |
| Input field | `TextInput` (client island) |
| Badge / tag | `Badge` |
| Layout stacks | `VStack` / `HStack` with `gap={n}` |
| Divider | `Divider` |
| Heading / body | `Heading level={n}` / `Text type="body" color="secondary"` |

Reference implementation: `src/app/pages/home.tsx`.

